messages.content:
Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants to turn on the Den Night Light to 70% brightness.
2. The ramp rate for Den Night Light should be set to 1 minute (which corresponds to enum value 12).
3. This action should trigger when the Office Pole Lamp is turned off.
4. "Turned off" is a COS event where the Office Pole Lamp's Status changes to 0% (Off).
5. The automation condition will check if Office Pole Lamp's Status is 0%.
6. The actions will set Den Night Light's Ramp Rate to 1 minute, then set On Level to 70%, and turn it On with 70% brightness.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on Den Night Light when Office Pole Lamp turns off",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Office Pole Lamp",
        "status": "Status",
        "value": 0,
        "uom": "%",
        "precision": 0
      }
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "device": "Den Night Light",
        "command": "Ramp Rate",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "RR", "value": 12, "uom": "enum", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "Den Night Light",
        "command": "On Level",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "OL", "value": 70, "uom": "%", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "Den Night Light",
        "command": "On",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "DON", "value": 70, "uom": "%", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
